DOCUMENT();       

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "extraAnswerEvaluators.pl"
           );
       
TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.


$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,4,1);
$b = random(5,8,1);
$c = random(2,6,1);
$d = random(2,3,1);
$f = random(4,8,1);

$b_cube = 0;
$b_square = $a*$d*$c;
$b_line = ($a*$f-$b)*$c;
$b_const = 0;

BEGIN_TEXT
Question 10:
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
Let $SPACE \( m(x) = $a x^2  - $b\) $SPACE , $SPACE \( n(x) = $c x \) $SPACE , and $SPACE \( o(x) = \sqrt{$d x + $f} \) .  Find a simplified formula for the  function below, and write your answer in the indicated form.  $BBOLD Under no circumstances should you leave any of the boxes blank. Use 0 as a place holder if you must.$EBOLD

$BR $SPACE $BR
\( m(o(x)) n(x) = \) \{ ans_rule(5) \} \( x^3 \) + \{ ans_rule(5) \} \( x^2 \) + \{ ans_rule(5) \} \( x \) +  \{ ans_rule(5) \}
$BR $SPACE $BR
Give your answer in the form \( Ax^3 + Bx^2 + Cx + D \) where $BITALIC A $EITALIC , $BITALIC B $EITALIC , $BITALIC C $EITALIC , and $BITALIC D $EITALIC are constants.  Thus in each blank above you simply need to enter a number (or zero if the term does not exist).  Be sure to account for subtraction by using negative coefficients.
$BR
END_TEXT

ANS( num_cmp( $b_cube ));
ANS( num_cmp( $b_square ));
ANS( num_cmp( $b_line ));
ANS( num_cmp( $b_const ));

$comp_line = $a*$d;
$comp_const = $a*$f-$b;

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR 
To find \( m \big( (o(x) \big) n(x) \), we first find
$BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ m \big( o(x) \big) = $a \big( \sqrt{$d x+$f} \big)^2 - $b \)
$BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ =  $a($d x + $f) - $b  \)
$BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ = $comp_line x + $comp_const \).
$BR $SPACE $BR
Then,
$BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ m \big( (o(x) \big) n(x) = ($comp_line x + $comp_const)($c x) \)
$BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ = $b_square x^2 + $b_line x \).
$BR 
END_SOLUTION


ENDDOCUMENT();
